<p><strong>Per-user E2 theme preferences.</strong></p>
<p><a href="#canned">Canned schemes</a></p>

<p>Colors can be any valid HTML color: Either hex triplets 
(<tt><b>#<font color="#c00000">RR</font><font color="#008000">GG</font><font color="#0000c0">BB</font></b></tt>) 
or named colors (e.g. <tt><span duh_style="font-weight: bold; background-color: papayawhip;">papayawhip</span></tt>). 
See [% linkNode( getNode( 'Named HTML Colors', 'superdoc' ) ) %] for some information that's actually useful. 
</p>

<p>Font information is expressed in [Cascading Style Sheets|CSS] terms: 12 pixels is 
expressed as "<tt>12px</tt>", 12 points is expressed as "<tt>12p<b>t</b></tt>". Font 
names are comma-separated lists, such as "<tt>Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif</tt>", where 
the browser tries to find the first one, then moves on down the list until it finds one 
that's installed on your computer.
</p>

